name: Pocketnotes Collection
description: Sometimes you need to write a thoughtful note-- but don't have a whole notesworth to say.  Say hello to pocketnotes: wallet-sized photos mounted to folding card stock.  No envelopes necessary.  These little notes are perfect for gift tags, flowers, thankyous, one-liners, apologies, and love notes.  The picture is worth a thousand words, so you only need room to write a few more.

name: Engrish Photocards
description:
Everyone knows english is cool.  But in Japan, there's nothing cooler.  So I've brought the best from Japan to you.  Since most of these photos were sniped from moving taxis and crowded sidewalks, they aren't masterpieces-- but the tshirts and billboards speak for themselves. And surprisingly, these ridiculous phrases can be inspiring and poignant too.  These cards know just what to say... "We're spending all the power for truly love!"

Each card is randomly selected from my collection.  And no matter how many you order, these handmade photocards are just $1 each, envelopes included.

name: Photocard Collection
description: If you can't pick just one, worry no more.  This collection of photocards includes twenty original photographs, randomly selected and mounted on folding cardstock.  Pretty outside, blank inside.  Twenty envelopes are included.

name: King
description: This handmade crown of thorns from the Salmon Creek trail in Vancouver, Washington and 150 year-old iron nails from the original Salt Lake Tabernacle are a personal expression of gratitude for the atonement of Jesus Christ.

name: Coke
description: My favorite drink (Diet, of course) sitting on the table at ZPies in Placerville, CA.  These prints are mounted to folding card stock.  Envelopes included. Cheers.
